# Styling Conventions

## Tailwind CSS 4

This project uses Tailwind CSS 4 with `@theme` directive for configuration.

### Theme Configuration

All theme variables are defined in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) using the `@theme` directive:

```css
@theme {
  /* Colors */
  --color-primary-500: #3b82f6;
  --color-primary-600: #2563eb;
  
  /* Typography */
  --font-family-sans: var(--font-inter), sans-serif;
  --font-family-mono: var(--font-jetbrains-mono), monospace;
  
  /* Spacing */
  --border-radius: 0.5rem;
  --shadow: 0 1px 3px 0 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
}
```

### Component Styles

Define reusable component classes in the `@layer components` section:

```css
@layer components {
  .dashboard-card {
    @apply bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg shadow-sm p-6 cursor-pointer;
  }
  
  .metric-card {
    @apply bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg shadow-sm p-6 
           hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-200 cursor-pointer 
           hover:scale-105 active:scale-95;
  }
  
  .status-badge {
    @apply inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium;
  }
}
```

## Styling Approach

### 1. Utility-First with Tailwind

Use Tailwind utilities directly in JSX for most styling:

```tsx
export const Card: React.FC<CardProps> = ({ children, className }) => {
  return (
    <div className={cn(
      'bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg shadow-sm p-6',
      'hover:shadow-md transition-shadow duration-200',
      className
    )}>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};
```

### 2. Component Classes for Reusable Patterns

Extract common patterns into component classes in `globals.css`:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Use component class for repeated patterns
export const MetricCard = () => (
  <div className="metric-card">
    <div className="metric-value">$2.4B</div>
    <div className="metric-label">Total Value Locked</div>
  </div>
);

// ❌ AVOID - Repeating the same long class strings
export const MetricCard = () => (
  <div className="bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg shadow-sm p-6 hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-200">
    {/* ... */}
  </div>
);
```

### 3. cn() Utility for Conditional Classes

Always use the `cn()` utility from [src/shared/utils/cn.ts](mdc:src/shared/utils/cn.ts) for merging classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/shared/utils/cn';

export const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps> = ({ 
  variant = 'primary', 
  className,
  disabled 
}) => {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        // Base styles
        'px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium transition-all duration-200',
        // Variant styles
        variant === 'primary' && 'bg-primary-600 text-white hover:bg-primary-700',
        variant === 'secondary' && 'bg-gray-200 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-300',
        // State styles
        disabled && 'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed',
        // Custom className from props
        className
      )}
      disabled={disabled}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

## Typography

### Font Configuration

Fonts are configured in [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx):

```typescript
import { Inter, JetBrains_Mono } from 'next/font/google';

const inter = Inter({ 
  subsets: ['latin'],
  variable: '--font-inter',
  display: 'swap',
});

const jetbrainsMono = JetBrains_Mono({
  subsets: ['latin'],
  variable: '--font-jetbrains-mono',
  display: 'swap',
});
```

### Typography Utilities

Use the predefined typography classes:

```tsx
// Display text - Large headings
<h1 className="text-display text-foreground">DeFi Dashboard</h1>

// Heading text - Section titles
<h2 className="text-heading text-foreground">Key Metrics</h2>

// Subheading text - Subsection titles
<h3 className="text-subheading text-foreground">Total Value Locked</h3>

// Body text - Paragraphs
<p className="text-body text-muted-foreground">Description text here</p>

// Caption text - Small labels
<span className="text-caption text-muted-foreground">Last updated</span>

// Monospace text - Addresses, code
<code className="text-mono text-foreground">0x1234...5678</code>
```

## Color System

### Semantic Colors

Use semantic color names defined in the theme:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Semantic colors
<div className="bg-surface text-foreground border-border">
<span className="text-primary-600">Primary action</span>
<span className="text-success">Success message</span>
<span className="text-error">Error message</span>

// ❌ AVOID - Direct color values
<div className="bg-white text-black border-gray-200">
<span className="text-blue-600">Action</span>
```

### Color Categories

- **Brand Colors**: `primary-*` (50-900)
- **Neutral Colors**: `gray-*` (50-900)
- **Status Colors**: `success`, `warning`, `error`, `info`
- **Semantic Colors**: `surface`, `foreground`, `muted`, `border`

## Responsive Design

### Breakpoints

Tailwind's default breakpoints:
- `sm`: 640px
- `md`: 768px
- `lg`: 1024px
- `xl`: 1280px
- `2xl`: 1536px

### Mobile-First Approach

Always use mobile-first responsive design:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Mobile-first
<div className="
  grid grid-cols-1 gap-4
  md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-6
  lg:grid-cols-4 lg:gap-8
">

// ❌ AVOID - Desktop-first
<div className="
  grid grid-cols-4 gap-8
  lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-6
  md:grid-cols-1 md:gap-4
">
```

## Interactive States

### Buttons

```tsx
<button className="
  px-4 py-2 rounded-lg
  bg-primary-600 text-white
  hover:bg-primary-700
  active:scale-95
  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-500
  disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed
  transition-all duration-200
">
  Click Me
</button>
```

### Cards

```tsx
<div className="
  bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg p-6
  hover:shadow-lg hover:scale-105
  active:scale-95
  transition-all duration-200
  cursor-pointer
">
  Card Content
</div>
```

### Links

```tsx
<a className="
  text-primary-600
  hover:text-primary-700 hover:underline
  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-500
  transition-colors duration-200
">
  Link Text
</a>
```

## Dark Mode Support

Prepare for dark mode using semantic colors:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD - Uses semantic colors that can adapt
<div className="bg-surface text-foreground">

// ❌ AVOID - Hard-coded light colors
<div className="bg-white text-black">
```

## Animation & Transitions

### Common Transitions

```css
/* Add to globals.css */
@layer components {
  .transition-smooth {
    @apply transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out;
  }
  
  .transition-fast {
    @apply transition-all duration-150 ease-in-out;
  }
  
  .hover-lift {
    @apply hover:scale-105 hover:shadow-lg transition-smooth;
  }
}
```

### Usage

```tsx
<div className="transition-smooth hover:bg-gray-100">
  Smooth transition
</div>

<div className="hover-lift cursor-pointer">
  Lifts on hover
</div>
```

## Best Practices

### DO's ✅

- Use `cn()` for combining classes
- Use semantic color names from theme
- Use component classes for repeated patterns
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use consistent spacing scale (4, 6, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, etc.)
- Use transition durations: 150ms, 200ms, 300ms
- Add focus states for accessibility
- Use `cursor-pointer` for clickable elements

### DON'Ts ❌

- Don't use arbitrary values unless absolutely necessary
- Don't repeat the same long class combinations
- Don't use hard-coded colors (use theme colors)
- Don't use `!important` in Tailwind classes
- Don't create custom CSS files for individual components
- Don't use inline styles (use Tailwind classes)
- Don't forget hover/focus/active states

## Class Organization

Order classes logically for readability:

```tsx
<div className={cn(
  // 1. Layout
  'flex items-center justify-between',
  // 2. Spacing
  'p-6 gap-4',
  // 3. Sizing
  'w-full h-auto',
  // 4. Typography
  'text-base font-medium',
  // 5. Colors
  'bg-surface text-foreground border-border',
  // 6. Borders & Shadows
  'border rounded-lg shadow-sm',
  // 7. Effects
  'hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-200',
  // 8. Interactivity
  'cursor-pointer',
  // 9. Custom classes
  className
)}>
```

